20 Sec. 3. 26 MRSA §664, sub-§4, as enacted by PL 2003, c. 423, §2 and affected by
21 §5, is amended to read:
22 4. Compensatory time. To the extent permitted under the federal Fair Labor
23 Standards Act of 1938, as amended, 29 United States Code, Section 207(o), the overtime
24 pay requirement applicable to executive or judicial employees as described in subsection
25 3, paragraph D may be met through compensatory time agreements. This subsection does
26 not apply to teachers employed by a school administrative unit or by the executive branch
27 of the State.
28 Sec. 4. 26 MRSA §670-A, as enacted by PL 2003, c. 423, §3 and affected by §5, is
29 amended to read:
30 §670-A. Remedies for overtime wage violations involving state employees
31 Notwithstanding section 670, in an action brought to recover unpaid overtime wages
32 for an employee of the executive or judicial branch of the State, except for teachers, the
33 judgment or award is limited to the unpaid overtime compensation adjudged to be due,
34 without liquidated damages or attorney's fees. An action for unpaid overtime wages for an
35 employee of the executive or judicial branch of the State, except for teachers, must be
