22 SUMMARY
2233 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, adds provisions that
2244 exclude teachers employed by school administrative units and the executive branch from
2255 the public employee exemption to entitlement to paid overtime. The amendment provides
2266 that teachers employed by the executive branch are entitled to the same remedies for
2277 overtime wage violations as workers not employed by the executive or judicial branch.
